# Task 1 - Updating System Package Repositories

## Problem Statement

Before installing any software, it is important to ensure the package manager has the latest information available from configured repositories.

An outdated package database may cause:

* installation failures
* outdated software deployments
* security vulnerabilities

The objective was to synchronize the local package index with remote package repositories.

---

# Command Used

```bash
sudo apt update
```

---

# Solution

```bash
labex:project/ $ sudo apt update
```

---

# Example Output

```bash
Hit:1 http://mirrors.cloud.aliyuncs.com/ubuntu jammy InRelease
Hit:2 http://mirrors.cloud.aliyuncs.com/ubuntu jammy-updates InRelease
Hit:3 http://mirrors.cloud.aliyuncs.com/ubuntu jammy-backports InRelease
Hit:4 http://mirrors.cloud.aliyuncs.com/ubuntu jammy-security InRelease

Reading package lists... Done
Building dependency tree... Done
Reading state information... Done

360 packages can be upgraded.
```

---

# Command Explanation

| Component | Purpose                                        |
| --------- | ---------------------------------------------- |
| `apt`     | Debian package management utility              |
| `update`  | Refresh local package repository information   |
| `sudo`    | Execute command with administrative privileges |

