# Task 5 - Cleaning Unused Dependencies

## Problem Statement

After uninstalling software, Linux may leave behind dependency packages that are no longer required.

These unused packages:

* consume disk space
* clutter the system
* provide no operational value

The objective was to remove orphaned dependencies.

---

# Command Used

```bash
sudo apt autoremove
```

---

# Solution

```bash
labex:project/ $ sudo apt autoremove
```

---

# Example Output

```bash
The following packages will be REMOVED:

gir1.2-libxfce4util-1.0
gir1.2-xfconf-0
gsfonts-x11
libdbus-glib-1-2
libgdk-pixbuf-xlib-2.0-0
libjpeg-turbo-progs
miscfiles
xscreensaver-data

After this operation, 5641 kB disk space will be freed.
```

---

# Command Explanation

| Component        | Purpose                    |
| ---------------- | -------------------------- |
| `apt autoremove` | Remove unused dependencies |
| `sudo`           | Administrative privileges  |

